# Tarteel Project Context

## Project Overview
Tarteel is a Vue.js application for Quranic text analysis and recitation. It provides tools for:
- Word and verse analysis
- Frequency charts and statistics
- Tarteel (recitation) features
- User authentication and profiles
- Notes and chat functionality

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Vue.js 3 with Composition API
- **UI Framework**: Vuetify
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth)
- **Build Tool**: Vite
- **Styling**: SCSS

## Key Architecture Patterns
- **Stores**: Pinia stores for state management (appStore, authStore, dataStore, notesStore, TarteelStore)
- **Components**: Modular Vue components organized by feature
- **Hooks**: Custom composables for reusable logic
- **Utils**: Utility functions for Arabic text processing, word filtering, etc.

## Important Conventions
- Always use early return patterns
- Follow Vue 3 Composition API patterns
- Maintain Arabic text handling utilities
- Follow existing component structure and naming conventions
-Always use vuetify for design and styling.
-Always minimal to zero css to achieve tasks

## Key Files to Understand
- `src/stores/` - State management
- `src/components/` - UI components organized by feature
- `src/utils/` - Utility functions for text processing
- `src/hooks/` - Custom composables
- `supabase/` - Database schema and migrations

## Common Tasks
- Arabic text processing and analysis
- Quranic data visualization
- User authentication and profile management
- Real-time data updates
- Mobile-responsive design 